name: Lat Lon Tools 3.6.5
body:
1. Lat Lon Tools can now snapshot H3 geohash coordinates and zoom to H3 coordinates. To enable H3 you will need to 'pip install h3' from the OSGeo4W Shell. Lat Lon Tools detects whether H3 is available or not and works as it always has without it.
2. Some coordinate formats represent a point on the earth's surface while others represent an area. Previously when using Lat Lon Tools' zoom to a coordinate tool it would zoom to the location and add a marker at the center of area coordinate formats. Now it marks the center but also displays the actual area the coordinate represents based on the resolution of the coordinate. This applies to H3, Geohash, Google Open Location Code (Plus Codes), and the amateur radio Maidenhead grid format.
3. You can now choose the color of the marker and grid outline used with the zoom to tool. It can be selected from the Settings dialog.

name: Lat Lon Tools 3.6.3
body: This release fixes a bug with the digitize tool when it is digitizing within a GeoPackage point layer.

name: Lat Lon Tools 3.6.2
body:
This adds two new expression functions: llt_dd and llt_yx. 
* llt_dd - This takes a coordinate and displays a decimal degree string.
* llt_yx - This takes a coordinate and displays it as a string in its native coordinate format.

This release also provide ECEF coordinate support.

name: Lat Lon Tools 3.5.10 Release
body: Includes several bug fixes and feature requests.

name: Lat Lon Tools 3.5.7
body: Fix of null geometry bug in the Point Layer to Fields algorithm.

name: Lat Lon Tools 3.5.6
body: Add plus code to_pluscode and from_pluscode field calculator functions.

name: Lat Lon Tools 3.5.3
body: This revamps the Coordinate Conversion dialog box to be more compact and adds UPS coordinates to it.  Coordinate capture and zoom to dialog also support UPS formatted coordinate strings.

name: Lat Lon Tools 3.5.2 Release
body:
1. Add a paste coordinate button to the zoom to coordinate dialog box.
2. Clean up documentation.
3. Remove vector conversion grouping.

name: Lat Lon Tools 3.5.0
body:
This version adds three new tools to copy a bounding box extent to the clipboard. These tools are:

1. Copy the canvas bounding box extent to the clipboard.
2. Copy selected area to an extent - Interactively select a region on the map to extract its bounding box extent and copy it to the clipboard.
3. Copy selected area to an extent - Copy the selected layer's extent. In some vector layers, this value may be estimated and not exact depending on how the layer was imported into QGIS.
4. Copy selected area to an extent - Copy the bounding box extent of selected features in a vector layer. If no features are selected then nothing will be copied. If the layer is not a vector layer, then the bounding box extent of the layer will be copied. In some vector layers, the bounding box extent may be estimated and not exact depending on how the layer was imported into QGIS.

name: Lat Lon Tools 3.4.5 Release
body:
* Adds settings menu to the toolbar
* Includes enhanced UTM parsing
* Updated open location code (Plus Code) library

name: Lat Lon Tools 3.4.2
body: UTM code was fixed to add in exception locations and UTM functions were exposed for the QGIS field calculator. Some DMS functions were also exposed to the field calculator.

name: Lat Lon Tools 3.4.1
body: This adds new MGRS functions for the field calculator. It also fixes a bug in the UTM module.

name: Lat Lon Tools 3.3.22
body: This release contains several bug fixes and enhancements to the coordinate conversion panel.

name: QGIS - 3.3.16 Release
body: This release includes padding with zeros for DMS coordinates and support for the maidenhead grid locator format, also known as QTH Locator and IARU Locator.

name: QGIS 3.3.14 Release
body: Updated the mgrs.py library to fix problems introduced by QGIS 3.10.

name: QGIS 3 - 3.3.13
body:
Changes Since 3.3.9 Release:
- Added degree and minute support.
- Made coordinate conversion dialog box dockable.
- Added zoom to button on coordinate conversions dialog box.
- Several bug fixes.

name: QGIS 3 - 3.3.9 Release
body: This version adds Geohash coordinate support.

name: QGIS 3 - 3.3.7 Release
body: Added enhancements to "Show in External Map". Open Street Map editor iD was added and the left and right mouse buttons were configured to show separate maps.

name: QGIS 3 - 3.3.5 Release
body: Enabled snapping with the External Map support tool.

name: QGIS 3 - 3.3.4 Release
body: This adds a new coordinate converter tool, provides Standard UTM support and enables the Copy Latitude, Longitude tool to interface with the QGIS snapping API so that exact coordinates from vector vertices can be copied to the clipboard.

name: QGIS 3 - 3.1.15 Release
body: This release adds Google Earth external map support.

name: QGIS 3 - 3.1.13 Release
body: Contains several bug fixes and enhancements.

name: QGIS 3 - 3.1.9 Release
body: Added a prefix and suffix to the coordinate capture output string.

name: QGIS 3 3.1.8 Release
body: This release supports various bounding box capture formats.

name: QGIS 3 - 3.1.5 release
body: Enhanced DDMMSS parsing

name: QGIS 2 - 1.1.3 release
body: Added enhanced DDMMSS parsing.
